    {
      "id": "q-8",
      "type": "long",
      "question": "If u = f(x-ct) + g(x+ct), prove that ∂²u/∂t² = c² ∂²u/∂x² (one-dimensional wave equation).",
      "marks": 10,
      "difficulty": "hard",
      "keyPoints": [
        "Let p = x-ct, q = x+ct",
        "∂u/∂t = f'(p)(-c) + g'(q)(c) = c[g'(q) - f'(p)]",
        "∂²u/∂t² = c[-g''(q)(c) - f''(-p)(c)] = -c²[g''(q) + f''(p)]",
        "Similarly ∂u/∂x = f'(p) + g'(q)",
        "∂²u/∂x² = f''(p) + g''(q)",
        "Therefore ∂²u/∂t² = c² ∂²u/∂x²"
      ]
    },
